NOTABLE DECISION:
Chose to build a shared CityServicePageTemplate instead of copy-pasting PPC city pages —
makes it trivial to scale to Phase 2 cities (remaining 16 OC + Riverside/SB/Ventura) by
adding entries to city-service-pages.ts with zero template changes. Trade-off: slightly
less city-specific hero imagery than the PPC template (no hero photo), compensated by
stronger conversion copy and faster page load.

NEXT SESSION SHOULD KNOW:
The [service]/[city] dynamic route uses getAllCityServiceParams() — to add new cities or
services, add entries to CITY_SERVICE_MAP in city-service-pages.ts and the route
automatically generates those static pages at build time. No route file changes needed.

Phase 1 pages built. Phase 2 (remaining cities) = add data entries only.
The /ac_repair → /air-conditioning/ac-repair redirect and mobile form single-step fixes
(mentioned in "Fix Before You Build") are NOT done — those require existing file edits
and were not part of this session's scope.

